name: Cool Fire Dice Tealight Holder (Each)
description:
A range of products made from recycled aircraft aluminium.. smooth, sparkling and sophisticated, these products are designed to impress with their clean lines and subtle design features. The perfect fusion of cool ice and hot fire, these products really come alive when the lights are down but are glossy enough to catch the eye at any time of the day.

SPECIAL OFFER

FREE BABY DICE with every Cool Fire Dice! ...worth £20!

name: Cool Baby Dice Tealight Holder (Each)
description:
Light up your own home or someone dear to you with this beautiful hand-finished dice tealight. So cool, and at such an unbeatable price!

SPECIAL OFFER

GET THIS COOL BABY DICE FREE when you buy one of our COOL FIRE DICE!

name: Champagne Flute Tealight Holder (Pair)
description: A weighty, tactile piece which would not be out of place at any celebration party, these flutes are a real talking point so closely do they resemble real flutes! Look inside and you will see the smooth cradle for a tealight. An altogether more sophisticated way to light up your life!  Finger print proof and with a velvet covered base, they are good to go on any surface.

name: Incense Holder (Each)
description:
Perfectly curved and balanced... holding the incence stick as if entranced at its tip, our sleek incense holder takes the burning of incense in your home to a whole new dimension! Hand finished from recycled sandcast aluminium, the holder is an elegant piece of design in its own right as well as a safe and functional way to experience aroma in your home.   
L 30cm, 600gms

name: Retro British Milk Bottle Vase
description: The Retro British Milk Bottle Vase is guaranteed to be popular and bring back memories of putting out the empties, your first home or student digs - Ecooldesigns is proud to present it's Retro British milk bottle vase!  Once again created from recycled sandcast aluminium, this smooth and shiny bottle is a faithful replica of the much loved shape. A real talking point for your kitchen table and the perfect home for your favourite flowers, ahhhhhh the memories!!!

name: Milk Bottle Vase (Each)
description:
Remember the ten green bottles hanging on a wall? Now see them taken to a new level as they are encased in recycled sandcast aluminium – making the perfect quirky vase for your favourite flowers. Smooth and tactile as with all the Cool Fire Range these milk bottle vases will catch and reflect the light. Coming soon – the traditional British Milk Bottle will get the Ecooldesigns treatment! H 21cm, W 775gms

SPECIAL OFFER

Now £30.00

name: Cool Bamboo Vase (Each)
description:
Perfect to display as a set of three, this fluid vase takes its inspiration from nature with a ridged design reflecting the natural sturdiness of bamboo. A piece you’ll want to pick up and marvel at. H 30cm

name: Folding Barrel Chair (Each)
description:
With an elegant arched design which shows it is easy in its own skin, our Barrel Chair is the perfect solution to entertaining indoors or out – or simply relaxing in the sun. Handmade from discarded Californian wine barrels, this award winning chair is unique to Ecooldesigns in Europe and the UK. Demonstrating an ingenuous design, each chair is made from salvaged 70 -gallon oak wine barrels, in a white oak colourway with smoky burgundy highlights.  Secured by 72 screws, the chair is easily folded with the slats resting alongside one another making it easy to store flat or transport to another location.

Delivery in time for Christmas.

name: Large Funnel Wire Basket in Full Rainbow
description:
Whether it's in a myriad of bright swirling colours or striking black and white, you will never tire of looking at the mesmerizing designs displayed in these highly functional and hard wearing wire baskets, hand woven in South Africa by Zulu tribespeople. 

Created from custom manufactured eco friendly lead-free wire, these baskets come in a variety of sizes and are ideal for storing fruit, bread or other foodstuffs - or simply to admire for their beauty. 

In choosing this product you are supporting a thriving cottage industry in South Africa of over 800 full-time weavers and their families who have applied their ancient weaving traditions to this new medium. 

To clean, simply wash the baskets in warm soapy water and look forward to many years of use around the home.

3 weeks delivery.
